Build
========

1. download toolchain and Ubuntu base from http://219.142.246.77:65000/sharing/5ajzpas1H
2. put them on the same level of bootloader-arm64 and linux-arm64, then unzip toolchain,
   no need to unzip distro, now you get the following folders:
   .
   ├── bootloader-arm64
   ├── distro
   │   └── distro_focal.tgz
   ├── gcc-linaro-6.3.1-2017.05-x86_64_aarch64-linux-gnu
   └── linux-arm64
3. $ sudo apt install bison flex bc rsync kmod cpio sudo \
                      uuid-dev cmake libssl-dev fakeroot \
                      dpkg-dev device-tree-compiler u-boot-tools \
                      uuid-dev libxml2-dev debootstrap \
                      qemu-user-static kpartx
4. $ source bootloader-arm64/scripts/envsetup.sh
5. $ build_bsp_without_package
6. copy '/home/linaro/bsp-debs/sophon-soc-libsophon*.deb' to /install/soc_bm1684/bsp-debs
   'libsophon*.deb' is cloned from https://github.com/sophgo/libsophon.git
   Compile with reference to SoC mode
7. download sdk from the official website
8. copy '/home/linaro/bsp-debs/sophon-mw-soc-sophon-ffmpeg*.deb' and '/home/linaro/bsp-debs/sophon-mw-soc-sophon-opencv*.deb' in '/sophon-sdk/sophon-mw' to /install/soc_bm1684/bsp-debs
9. $ build_package
